Example SDTM Laboratory Test Results Data

sdtm_example_dataverse_lb.Rd

Example SDTM Laboratory Test Results Data

Usage

sdtm_example_dataverse_lb

Format

A data frame with 29 variables and 83 observations:

STUDYID

Study Identifier, character

DOMAIN

Domain Abbreviation, character

USUBJID

Unique Subject Identifier, character

LBSEQ

Sequence Number, numeric

LBREFID

Specimen ID, character

LBTESTCD

Lab Test or Examination Short Name, character

LBTEST

Lab Test or Examination Name, character

LBCAT

Category for Lab Test, character

LBSCAT

Subcategory for Lab Test, character

LBORRES

Result or Finding in Original Units, character

LBORRESU

Original Units, character

LBORNRLO

Reference Range Lower Limit in Orig Unit, character

LBORNRHI

Reference Range Upper Limit in Orig Unit, character

LBSTRESC

Character Result/Finding in Std Format, character

LBSTRESN

Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units, numeric

LBSTRESU

Standard Units, character

LBSTNRLO

Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units, numeric

LBSTNRHI

Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units, numeric

LBSTNRC

Reference Range for Char Result-Std Units, character

LBNRIND

Reference Range Indicator, character

LBSPEC

Specimen Type, character

LBMETHOD

Method of Test or Examination, character

LBBLFL

Baseline Flag, character

LBFAST

Fasting Status, character

VISITNUM

Visit Number, numeric

VISIT

Visit Name, character

VISITDY

Planned Study Day of Visit, numeric

LBDTC

Date/time of Specimen Collection, character, ISO 8601

LBDY

Study Day of Specimen Collection, numeric

Source

https://doi.org/10.7910/DVN/51B6NK
